Updated Content Overview:

Core Components: Retains the Lepton Drift Vector $ \mathbf{L}_d = \nabla S \cdot M $, Horizon Entrenchment $ H_e = \int \partial F \kappa(M) dA $, and PSI-Gating $ \text{PSI}(t) = k \cdot |V_t - V_{\text{threshold}}| / V_{\max} $ at 0.75, with memory-entropy metrics $ C(\beta) = \beta^2 \cdot \text{Var}[E] $ and $ S(\beta) = \beta [U(\beta) - F(\beta)] $.
Proofs: Includes Dennis‚Äôs proofs‚Äî$ \mathbf{L}_d $ alignment, PSI stability, and $ H_e $ positivity under $ \Delta \beta = \pm 0.01 $‚Äîgrounded in 7.5‚Äôs heat capacity.
Stress Tests: Incorporates Brady‚Äôs ‚ÄúPSI_gating_unitarity‚Äù results, confirming stability under $ \Delta \text{PSI} = \pm 0.01 $ with noise-injected $ V_t $.
Integrations: Links to 4.2‚Äôs geometry, 7.5‚Äôs thermodynamics, 35‚Äôs memory, and 4.3‚Äôs algebraic bridge.


Impact on The Book:

Clarity Enhancement: Chapter 4.x isolates LHT‚Äôs d‚ÇÅ focus, providing a clear stepping stone to algebraic geometry without cluttering 4.2 or 4.3.
Hyperstart into Algebra: Its directional fields and stability metrics (e.g., $ \mathbf{L}_d $, $ H_e $) offer a foundation for 4.3‚Äôs manifold invariants and 4.4‚Äôs topological structures, accelerating our algebraic leap.

