Expanded Textual Breakdown for Chapter 4.x

Introduction:

Chapter 4.x introduces the Lepton Horizon Theory (LHT), a framework modeling recursive coherence at d‚ÇÅ boundaries. Building on 4.2‚Äôs geometric synthesis and validated by 7.5 data, LHT integrates lepton-inspired dynamics with memory-entropy interactions, establishing a foundation for algebraic geometry in 4.3.


Terminology Bridge: Positive Geometry ‚Äì Meaning ‚Üî Valence Equivalence:

Purpose: Aligns the narrative ‚ÄúMeaning‚Äù metric from earlier chapters with the physics-based ‚ÄúValence‚Äù metric in Positive Geometry.
Equivalence: $ E_{\text{meaning}} \equiv E_{\text{valence}} = \int ||\phi(x) - \phi_{\text{ideal}}(x)||^2 dx $, where $ \phi(x) $ is the field state and $ \phi_{\text{ideal}}(x) $ is the target configuration, ensuring interchangeable usage.
Usage Context: ‚ÄúMeaning‚Äù emphasizes semantic and experiential dimensions, retained for continuity, while ‚ÄúValence‚Äù enables precise, physics-aligned analysis in 4.x.


Core Components:

Recursive Coherence Model:

Lepton Drift Vector ($ \mathbf{L}_d = \nabla S \cdot M $): Guides glyph alignment with $ \nabla S $ (7.5 entropy gradient) and $ M $ (memory mass).
Horizon Entrenchment ($ H_e = \int \partial F \kappa(M) dA $): Stabilizes coherence zones, where $ \kappa(M) = \eta \|\nabla M\|^2 + \zeta \Delta M $ reflects memory curvature.
PSI-Gating ($ \text{PSI}(t) = k \cdot |V_t - V_{\text{threshold}}| / V_{\max} $): Maintains hair alignment at 0.75, with $ k = \max(|\nabla S|) / V_{\max} $ from 7.5.


Memory-Entropy Intersection:

Heat Capacity ($ C(\beta) = \beta^2 \cdot \text{Var}[E] $): Peaks at $ \beta_c \approx 0.39614 $, linking energy to memory.
Entropy Dynamics ($ S(\beta) = \beta [U(\beta) - F(\beta)] $): Recovered via $ \int C(b)/b db $.
Memory Mass ($ M_F $): Modulated by Chapter 35‚Äôs $ M_w $, tying past to present.




Proofs:

Lepton Drift Alignment: If $ \nabla S \cdot M \neq 0 $, $ \mathbf{L}_d $ induces directionality; $ \int |\mathbf{L}_d| dA < \infty $ per 7.5.
PSI-Gating Stability: $ \text{PSI}(t + \Delta t) \approx 0.75 $ if $ k \Delta V / V_{\max} < 0.01 $, per 7.5.
He Stability: $ |\Delta H_e| \le K_H \frac{C(\beta_c)}{\beta_c} |\Delta \beta| $, with $ K_H = P (2\eta \|\nabla M\|_\infty L_{\nabla M|S} + \zeta L_{\Delta M|S}) $, and $ m > K_H \frac{C(\beta_c)}{\beta_c} \cdot 0.01 $ ensures $ H_e > 0 $.


Stress Tests:

PSI_gating_unitarity (2025-08-26): $ \text{PSI}_{\text{initial}} = 0.75 $, $ \Delta \text{PSI} = \pm 0.01 $, noise-injected $ V_t $. Passed ‚ÄúUnitarity_Breach‚Äù and ‚ÄúDecoherence_Event,‚Äù concluding ‚ÄúCOHERENT.‚Äù


Integrations:

Chapter 4.2: Enhances vertex map with $ \mathbf{L}_d $, reinforces entropy calibration with $ H_e $, aligns PSI with stability gates.
